According to Watkins (2021), items should be removed if they have skewness > 2.0 or kurtosis > 7.0. These items would violate the assumptions of the Pearson correlation coefficients that factor analysis is based on. (Do we need to consider the items as ordinal discrete values?)

items with kurtosis > 7.0 include * Agg09, * Agg11, * Agg12, * Agg13, * Agg15, * Agg17, * Agg19, * Fear21, * Fear23, * Fear24, * Fear25, * Misc55, * Misc58, * Misc68, * Misc69
